RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 89. Maiden Special Weight Purse 82000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KISSED BY FIRE sped to the front from inside, opened up in the two path around the bend, two to three wide into the stretch, padded the lead in upper stretch and was ridden out to the wire. MAKE IT SNOW settled at the back and steered inward, got boxed in along the rail through the turn, angled out into the clear and finished well to best the rest. THIRTY CARATS tracked outside a rival early, coaxed two wide around the turn and lacked a bid in the stretch. CALMING SEA chased along the inside to the stretch and weakened. CHRISTINA'S CANDY forwardly placed two wide into the turn, moved out to the three path around the bend, spun four wide into the lane and also weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 30000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.

CLAIM.OWNER: David A Bernsen LLC and Lambert Jeffrey

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOT ROD MAMA broke a step slow, tucked inside at the back, advanced up the backstretch, challenged inside the top pair entering the stretch, took over outside the eighth pole and prevailed over MODERA in the final strides. MODERA vied inside a pair of rivals early then chased in the two path around the clubhouse turn, launched a bid three wide outside the leader at the five-sixteenths pole, fought three deep in the lane and finished gamely to the wire. SWEET HELLO vied between foes then cleared around the first turn and moved inside, met the bid from MODERA around the far turn, showed the way two wide into the stretch, lost command to HOT ROD MAMA approaching the eighth pole and stayed on while outkicked by the top pair. ZZYZX settled in the two path, shifted three wide into the lane and could not rally. COMPTONS HOUSE sat off the pace three wide into the first turn, moved in and saved ground through the final turn but weakened in the drive. MAGAZINE chased four wide early, checked and had to alter when forced wide by LOVE OUR FAMILY pulling up on the clubhouse turn, moved back in approaching the backstretch, coaxed three deep in the middle stages, trailed into the far turn, eased on that bend and down the lane and walked off. LOVE OUR FAMILY vied three deep into the first turn before being pulled up and taken out wide around the bend and walked into the van following the race.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE'S RESILIENT dueled for the lead from inside, brushed with outer opponent at the five-sixteenths pole, cleared past the quarter pole, lugged out through the lane and drew away. SHE'S INTHEARMYNOW dueled outside SHE'S RESILIENT, brushed midway around the turn, fought to the quarter pole, chased that rival into and down the stretch and held the place. SILVER LIGHTENING broke a step slow, stalked the top pair from inside and got edged for the show honors. MINEDANDREFINED broke a step slow, chased outside a rival to the turn, closest in pursuit of the dueling pair around the turn and flattened out in the stretch run. UNA PALABRA tracked off the rail, rounded the bend two then three wide and could not rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISTY MUPPET stalked between early then lost path and altered inward, chased along the rail into the turn, rushed up inside the leader and snuck through while brushing with that rival, took over past the quarter pole, put away BEAU SOLEIL past the eighth pole and drew off under mild urging. BEAU SOLEIL broke a step slow and veered out leaving the gate, rushed to the front and cleared the field then crossed over, was challenged by MISTY MUPPET nearing the quarter pole, lost command late on the bend, fought to the eighth pole but was no match for the winner in the late stages while clearly second best. CAPO SORELLA away quickly in the beginning then chased BEAU SOLEIL up the backstretch, boxed in at the five-sixteenths pole, chased two wide into the lane, lacked a rally but held the show. MISS PIXY STIX shifted out leaving the gate, chased four deep early, three deep on the turn then three wide into the lane and flattened. AMERICAN TSUNAMI chased between foes then suffered a mild shuffle early on the turn, exited the bend four wide and weakened. IFUAINTFIRSTURLAST chased between foes then got put in tight at the seven-sixteenths pole and weakened. FIFTY STARS broke awkwardly, saved ground around the turn at the back and was not a factor. HIGH FLYING GRACIE was off slow to begin, raced outside a rival at the back, three wide into the lane and failed to menace.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILL BE set the pace inside a pair of rivals into and around the turn, shook loose past the quarter pole and drew away under left and right handed urging. ARROWTHEGREAT attended the pace three deep early, chased the winner three wide into the lane, could not summon the needed late kick in the final furlong but stayed on to secure second. BYE BYE RAY stalked two wide into the turn, spun three wide into the lane, tipped out in the stretch and could not get by ARROWTHEGREAT for the place honors. BAD SNEAKERS pressed WILL BE from between runners, could not keep pace with that rival past the quarter pole and weakened in the final furlong. MIXTO chased inside a trio of rivals up the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, moved out in the lane but failed to threaten. BROADWAY UNIONS tracked four deep early on, came five wide into the stretch and proved no menace. AARON chased three deep between rivals up the backstretch, rounded the bend three then four wide and lacked a rally. NO SECRET was off slow then hard to ride leaving the gate, dropped far back early and never got involved.

CLAIM.OWNER: Holleman John and O'Neill Doug F

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STORM THE NIGHT cleared and crossed over, led a bit off the rail through the turn, set down into the stretch and remained comfortably in front through the final furlong under a drive. CENTRAL DISPATCH stalked STORM THE NIGHT four deep, three deep past the five-sixteenths pole, closest in pursuit entering the final furlong, could not make any headway on the winner but was clearly second best. TOKAMAK raced in mid-pack then drew closer leaving the backstretch, rounded the bend four then five wide and got up for the show honors. CAPTAIN SPARROW chased between foes in the two path into and around the bend, failed to summon the needed rally in the drive and got outfinished for third. HAPPY TEARS broke a step slow on the outside, traveled near the back three wide into the turn, moved into the two path leaving the bend and showed a mild response to improve position. CHAOS REIGNS stalked the pace from inside, asked around the turn, saved ground to the stretch and weakened. PRAY FOR ME RAY was off slow to begin, trailed up the backstretch, angled out while splitting foes at the quarter pole, came five wide into the lane and improved position. FOREIGN INFLUENCE got bumped leaving the gate, put in tight between runners early, started to climb up the backstretch, ran up on behind a rival and had to steady at the half-mile pole, got floated six wide on the turn and could not rally after a rough trip. EMERALD UNION settled off the pace on the inside and lacked a rally. BURTON WAY broke in and bumped, tracked three wide into the turn, moved out four wide and went between runners at the five-sixteenths pole and weakened down the lane. BENDETTIJOE stalked three deep between rivals, started to weaken and dropped back around the bend and tired in the lane.
